					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>A teacher of rhetoricians.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						( Apollonius, in sermone semper
						Atticus: in scriptis, semper adamantinus. )
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Apollonius of Tyana"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>Apollonius, always Athenian in his speech; always incorruptible in his writings.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						Pilula[e] aura[e].
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>Golden pills.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						( Rudis est, qui non est elegans: qui affectare
						| videtur, magis rudis. )
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>He, who is not elegant, is rude. He, who seems to aspire, is ruder.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="EN">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
					<marginalia_text>
						As acts; so termes woold be effectual.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
		</marginalia>
		
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="EN">
				<position book_orientation="90" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						He that doth not allwais thinke upon it, To make his vtterance reddie, flowing, and
						pithie without Circumlocution, or anie delaie: shall sumtime be slowe, coold, or sumway
						harsh. Which ar vile faults in nimble, and fine vtterance: &amp; argu a 
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="90" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						simple conceit, or base gift of Nature.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="EN">
				<position book_orientation="90" place="right_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Nothing delightes, or deserues commendation, that is not quick, apt, round, &amp; pithie
						to the point: or seemes not to flowe of the owne accord. Naturally.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
		</marginalia>
		
